  <h1>Steer Clear Web App</h1>

  <span class="content"> The Steer Clear Ride Request web application was developed using the <a href="http://rubyonrails.org/">Ruby on Rails</a> framework by WM graduate students Philip Steele and Alex Atkins. </span>
  <span class="content"> This is an open source project, and this implementation is free to use by the WM community for the Steer Clear service.  </span>
  <span class="content"> Our code is available at <a href="https://github.com/pdsteele/steerclear">https://github.com/pdsteele/steerclear</a>.</span>

  <h2>Data Collection</h2>
  <span class="content"> The ride request data collected using this application will be anonymized and used for research to help improve the Steer Clear service. </span>
  <span class="content"> Data used for this research includes the ride request time, pick-up location, drop-off location, the size of your party, and the approximate time you were picked up. </span>
  <span class="content"> If you do not agree with this usage, please contact Steer Clear (<a href="mailto:steerclear@email.wm.edu">steerclear@email.wm.edu</a>) after your ride to request exclusion from the research.  </span>

